oint of audio and visual materialities, cultural practices and perceptual activity.The interdisciplinary approach adopted by the book makes its discussion of sound of interest to those studying and working in a range of subject disciplines, including film studies, sound studies, sonic arts, cultural studies, music and art history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSound in motion pictures. 0aSound motion pictures. 0aSoundxRecording and reproducing. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aFive Film Exercises.  aJohn Smith.  aMichel Chion.  aWarner Bros.  aWhitney Brothers.  acartoon sound.  acinesonic codes.  acinesonic text.  aclassical film practice.  afilm materiality.  afilm soundtracks.  aground noise.  aoptical crackle.  asonic presences.  asound mirrors.  asound-image relations.  astrange sounds.  awarning system.1 aBirtwistle, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612969740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129697423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129697/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles